{"id":"d=origam-topic-3918//p=5d188e21e6984a16936bab57392ee3b9","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-3918"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["cfbae9884f68449e8b129bed1a2d19ab"],"__file_part":["852e171dbf344c1b81684c4e698c037f"],"__part_n":["2"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"topicId":["3918"],"categoryId":["61"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-view-the-application-database/3918"],"title":["How to view the application database"],"imagesFound":["9"],"imagesDescribed":["9"],"imageUrl":["https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/f/ffcafb0db0169ba5b189e822e850b6a2e3eae3f9.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/c/c30f912394921f448d878ae5dfbb110107086201.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/4/431df366e549099d584959cb9434b24c9a551d59.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/2/2760c5fa61e269064969f35f2202384cc5880d09.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/a/a6ac0c76ff83854782d58d30cc5b657780457273.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e8a96e11f618785fe6f356df4c4a3621d434c125.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/ecb02e9ecbdd91579d43283f03e8c0e9033f6f2c.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/9/9c6c0b3449bf9820432a81c273e4b47f5e85c144.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/5aa8a69461b9ab676b9cc1b183cffb25b49c4b2e.png"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":" server configuration interface for a software application, likely CloudBeaver. Key sections include \u0022Server Information\u0022 with fields for \u0022Server Name,\u0022 \u0022Server URL,\u0022 and \u0022Session lifetime, min.\u0022 The \u0022Configuration\u0022 options have toggle switches for \u0022Enable private connections\u0022 and \u0022Navigator simple view.\u0022 In the \u0022Resource Manager,\u0022 there\u0027s an option to \u0022Enable Resource Manager.\u0022 The \u0022Authentication Settings\u0022 section includes toggles for \u0022Allow anonymous access,\u0022 \u0022LDAP,\u0022 \u0022Reverse proxy,\u0022 and \u0022Local.\u0022 In the \u0022Security\u0022 subsection, there are switches for \u0022Save credentials\u0022 and \u0022Save users credentials.\u0022 The \u0022Disabled Drivers\u0022 section lists drivers like DuckDB and SQLite. The purpose of the interface is to manage server settings and connection configurations.\n\n\n  \n After that, you can connect to your database server: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e8a96e11f618785fe6f356df4c4a3621d434c125.png]\nDescription: The image depicts a user interface for configuring a SQL Server connection within a database management application. The visible section includes fields for entering connection details under \u0022Driver Properties.\u0022 The user can select \u0022SQL Server\u0022 as the driver and choose between \u0022Manual\u0022 or \u0022URL\u0022 configuration. Key fields are \u0022Host\u0022 (with the value 172.17.0.4), \u0022Port\u0022 (set to 1433), and \u0022Database\u0022 (designated as master). Authentication options include \u0022SQL Server Authentication\u0022 with fields for \u0022User name\u0022 (defaulting to sa) and \u0022User password.\u0022 Additional checkboxes for \u0022Save credentials for all users with access,\u0022 \u0022Show all schemas,\u0022 and \u0022Trust Server Certificate\u0022 are present. Buttons labeled \u0022CANCEL,\u0022 \u0022TEST,\u0022 and \u0022SAVE\u0022 are also visible. This interface is designed for establishing and testing connections to a SQL Server database.\n\n\n  \n Please note that you need to address the DB Server (host) by its IP address, as using localhost with a port will probably not work in this scenario. \n To get the DB Server IP address, run the following command: \n  docker inspect container_name  (container_name = name of your container with the DB Server) \n Any issues, you can consult with your favourite AI advisor   \n\n---\n\n@vikter (2025-09-23 07:46:00Z):\n Another option is using Visual Studio Code and the DB Code Database Management Plugin: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/ecb02e9ecbdd91579d43283f03e8c0e9033f6f2c.png]\nDescription: The image features a software management interface for \u0022DBCode - Database Management.\u0022 The UI includes the logo consisting of three horizontal purple lines and text displaying \u0022DBCode\u0022 followed by a website link (dbcode.io). Below this, there is a download count of \u002283,867\u0022 and a rating of \u00224.5 stars\u0022 based on 48 reviews. The description states that DBCode can connect to various databases, including PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQL Server, SQLite, Mongo, Oracle, and DuckDB. Visible action buttons include \u0022Disable,\u0022 \u0022Uninstall,\u0022 and an auto-update checkbox. The apparent purpose of this interface is to manage database connections and software functionalities for users.\n\n\n  \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/9/9c6c0b3449bf9820432a81c273e4b47f5e85c144.png]\nDescription: The context of the image appears to be a SQL Server Management tool interface displaying a database structure alongside a table view. The left panel shows a hierarchy of database objects under the \u0022Connections\u0022 section, including tables, columns, primary key, foreign keys, indexes, views, stored procedures, and functions of an \u0022appdemo\u0022 database housed within a SQL Server Docker environment. The right panel contains a table titled \u0022OrigamUser\u0022 which lists six entries with columns: RecordCreated, RecordUpdated, LastLoginDate, LastLockoutDate, and FailedPassword. The specific dates recorded range from 1900-01-01 to more recent dates in 2025, along with timestamps. The interface indicates an executed query with a processing time of 27ms for retrieving six rows.\n\n\n  \n In VS Code you can manage also Docker containers and do a lot of other things, and it is for free. \n\n---\n\n@vikter (2026-05-01 06:03:38Z):\n Yet another option is  DBGate  which has also a free open-source community edition. \n This solution has a very user-friendly and practical front-end, and most importantly,  it\u2019s a web application that can run locally in a Docker container . ","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:41:52"},"vector":[-0.031058097,0.025235713,-0.07975633,0.007998313,-0.03635682,-0.032129288,0.03936228,-0.016789565,0.05227523,0.045178782,0.029851267,-9.17473E-05,0.015705496,0.0031150263,-0.013799291,0.011195533,-0.013548066,0.006758081,0.019892788,0.02055946,-0.0045597786,-0.011803359,0.034660913,0.0073488704,-0.014848037,-0.012397155,-0.033807088,-0.022920543,0.0013505819,0.043412514,0.0034153892,-0.051285584,0.0017801406,0.002480878,0.023989897,-0.044136256,0.015142836,-0.0058962493,-0.04452433,-0.009398217,-0.008705126,-0.0060673635,0.0064230803,0.024140822,0.038852032,-0.047279216,-0.024947591,0.005775952,-0.0148657,-0.003615469,-0.040715393,-0.02466636,0.03428379,-0.029461905,0.004016462,0.023530666,-0.015485553,0.0037898945,-0.04786604,0.006688891,-0.002972024,0.0050517246,-0.0012243274,-0.017391356,0.018442865,0.004185792,-0.03383708,0.041113585,-0.017372282,-0.022737391,0.016820922,0.011251557,-0.04782548,-0.014521577,-0.069596305,-0.0033114683,0.01208635,0.011012232,-0.018054629,0.022570666,-0.010258299,0.021317594,0.0143131735,0.0010103611,-0.03433098,0.01786457,-0.034088276,0.08229515,0.01573507,0.01490178,-0.0003082703,-0.030160945,0.040987194,-0.0045857774,-0.048716556,-0.01633612,0.0034689573,0.0053169644,0.021984123,-0.00031952377,-0.047379773,-0.038572412,0.0010057478,-0.01658121,0.0022618896,-0.0024157714,0.03105353,-0.01647644,-0.013456811,-0.04244225,0.022263817,0.040418442,0.026264416,-0.016456218,-0.000929534